Certainly! It seems that the error is occurring because the pattern character 'T' in the date format is not recognized. To resolve this issue, you can modify the code as follows:

In KafkaEventErrorHandler.java, update the handleError method as follows:

```java
import org.slf4j.Logger;
import org.slf4j.LoggerFactory;
import org.springframework.kafka.listener.ListenerExecutionFailedException;
import org.springframework.kafka.support.converter.MessageConverter;
import org.springframework.kafka.support.serializer.DeserializationException;
import org.springframework.kafka.support.serializer.ErrorHandlingDeserializer2;

public class KafkaEventErrorHandler extends ErrorHandlingDeserializer2 {

    private static final Logger LOGGER = LoggerFactory.getLogger(KafkaEventErrorHandler.class);
    
    public KafkaEventErrorHandler(MessageConverter messageConverter) {
        super(messageConverter);
    }

    @Override
    public Object handleError(Message<?> message, ListenerExecutionFailedException exception, Consumer<?, ?> consumer) {
        if (exception.getCause() instanceof DeserializationException) {
            // Handle deserialization errors
            DeserializationException deserializationException = (DeserializationException) exception.getCause();
            LOGGER.error("Exception while deserializing Json. Message - {}", deserializationException.getMessage());
        } else {
            // Log other types of errors
            LOGGER.error("Error while processing message: {}", exception.getMessage());
        }
        // Return null to skip processing the message further
        return null;
    }
}
```

In the logAuditData method, update the date format pattern to use single quotes for the literal 'T':

```java
import java.text.SimpleDateFormat;
import java.util.Collections;
import java.util.Date;
import java.util.UUID;

public class YourClass {

    public UnifiedAuditMessage logAuditData(UnifiedAuditMessage auditMsg, String fileType, ResponseEntity<String> errorMessage) {
        SimpleDateFormat dateFormat = new SimpleDateFormat("yyyy-MM-dd'T'HH:mm:ss");
        String currentDate = dateFormat.format(new Date());

        return new UnifiedAuditMessage(
                auditMsg.getInputFilePath(),
                auditMsg.getUrl(),
                auditMsg.getPort(),
                auditMsg.getOutputFilePath(),
                auditMsg.getDelimiters(),
                fileType,
                currentDate,
                currentDate,
                auditMsg.getNo_of_records_in_the_file(),
                auditMsg.getNo_of_records_processed(),
                auditMsg.getNo_of_records_failed(),
                UUID.randomUUID(),
                UUID.randomUUID(),
                Collections.singletonList(errorMessage.getStatusCode().toString()),
                auditMsg.getCollector_id(),
                JobStatus.COLLECTION_FAILED
        );
    }
}
```

Make sure to update any import statements if necessary.

